# Building the model

Canonical references: [ARCHITECTURE.md](../../ARCHITECTURE.md), [docs/domain-specification.md](../../docs/domain-specification.md).

## Before any change

1. Read **domain specification** (Ubiquitous Language) for ticket, workflow, project, or notification work.
2. Read **ARCHITECTURE.md** §5 (package layout), §11 (naming), §12 (feature workflow).
3. Follow patterns in the package you edit.

## Domain vocabulary in code and tests

- Use domain terms: `Ticket`, `Workflow`, `Transition`, `Subscriber`, `Identifier` — not `Data`, `ItemDTO`, `stateFlag`.
- Test names: `shouldMoveTicketWhenTransitionIsValid()` — full narrative in [issues-tests.mdc](issues-tests.mdc).

## Package placement

| Change | Package |
|--------|---------|
| Auth, JWT, login | `auth` |
| Users, roles | `user` |
| Projects | `project` |
| Workflows, statuses, transitions | `workflow` |
| Tickets, comments, history | `ticket`, `ticket.*` |
| Categories | `categories` |
| SSE notifications | `notifications` |
| Dashboard widgets | `dashboards` |
| Email | `mailer` |
| Cross-cutting HTTP/errors | `infra` |

Bounded context rules: [issues-bounded-contexts.mdc](issues-bounded-contexts.mdc).

